The paper deals with privacy-type properties of security protocols, which are often modelled using process algebras. The focus is on deciding trace equivalence properties using symbolic execution and constraint solving. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with security protocols, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of process algebras and symbolic execution also suggests that the paper could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with optimization techniques for reducing the combinatorial explosion problem, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
